main event: A report was prepared regarding the sighting of a flying saucer in the Washington State area on July 21, 1950.
interesting points: The report indicates prior interest in flying saucers by Chief Kinzel of the Washington State Patrol., Confidential information was shared with the intelligence section regarding an object seen in the Hover Hills., The documented object was described as having written material on it related to the Hanford atomic project., Some objects were noted to be piloted by humans while others were controlled by atomic energy., The report raised concerns about potential missile launches from bodies of water.
witness description: Lt. Rolland L Snille and Chief Kinzel from the Washington State Patrol.
